There is a graffiti in my hood under a train bridge, very old, been there for like 40 years, used to disturb me as a kid. It's on the wall, a bunch of heads and hands, and a third of the heads are twice as big as the rest, and every head has hands that hold the smaller heads.

The large heads are smiling sardonically, in a cruel way, and the small heads are in distress or sad. Basically shows the big oppressing the small. Might be done by older students bragging about bullying, might be by hood rats, "being big on the street". Very neo-Darwinian.
